    <h1>The settlement: where it goes.</h1>
    <p class="lead">In 2023 the 21 Robinson Huron Treaty nations reached a settlement of about $10 billion for past annuities, paid half by Canada and half by Ontario, after the courts found the Crown had failed for generations to raise the $4 annuity with the wealth taken from the land. The money has flowed to the communities. This page lays out, in plain terms and from public sources, what is settled and what members are still asking. It takes no side; it points you to what the documents say.</p>
  </div>
